This is a GNN model which tries to predict the probability of each setup assignments

We use bipartite graph. 
We separate the set of variable nodes and constraint nodes.Then use the coeffients in the MILP formulation to assign features and attribute for each node and edge.

compared to v01, we add a dummy product, so that the constraints \sum_{j}Y_{j,r}=1 holds. Then we use softmax to predict the probability in each period.

We add the information from relaxation problem, including the optimal relaxed solution and the dual values, to the features of nodes and constraints.

We report the relative gap and time using the gnn predicted decisions.
- in det-v3, we add only the term M(1-y) if the probability p is above a certain threshold
- compared to det-v3, here the penalization term is M((1-p)y + p(1-y)) for all the y, use directly the predicted value p in the objective function
